== Roasted Potato Chunks ==

Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut @potato{2} into bite-sized chunks.

Place on a lined #oven tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%drizzle}, season with
@salt{} and toss to coat.

Roast until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Parmesan Garlic Crumb ==

Meanwhile, halve @Kumato{2}. Finely chop @garlic{1}(finely chopped).

In a #small bowl{}, combine garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{1%packet}, @Parmesan
cheese{1%packet}, a pinch of salt and a good drizzle of @olive oil{}.

== Chicken ==

While kumato is roasting, place your hand flat on top of @chicken breast{660%g}
and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @lemon pepper seasoning{1%sachet}, a drizzle of
@olive oil{} and a pinch of salt. Add chicken steaks, turning to coat.

In a #large frying pan{}, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} over medium-high heat.

Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side (cook in
batches if your pan is getting crowded).

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

== Roasted Kumato ==

Place tomato on a second lined oven tray. Spoon Parmesan garlic crumb over
tomatoes and drizzle with @olive oil{}.

Roast until tomatoes are just blistered and crumb is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

== Salad ==

In a second #medium bowl{}, combine @mixed salad leaves{1%packet}, a drizzle of
@balsamic vinegar{1%drizzle} and @olive oil{}. Season.

== To Serve ==

Divide potato chunks, chicken, salad and roasted Parmesan crumb kumato between
plates. Serve with @Italian truffle mayonnaise{1%packet}. Enjoy!